<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I’m using the native Windows emacs app, and SyncThing to sync files between computers that I move between throughout the day, and I want the files to automatically stay in sync without having to <code>revert-buffer</code> all the time. </p> <p>I used to use just the following for my <code>auto-revert-mode</code> config:</p> <pre><code>(global-auto-revert-mode 1) </code></pre> <p>but I noticed it wasn’t consistent in catching changes. So I did some research and found some suggested changes <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41446667/why-is-global-auto-revert-mode-not-reverting-my-buffer">here</a> and <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6512086/emacs-reverts-buffer-to-weird-previous-state-with-git-rebase">here</a> that I tried in my config:</p> <pre><code>(custom-set-variables &#39;(auto-revert-remote-files t) &#39;(auto-revert-interval 10) &#39;(auto-revert-verbose nil) </code></pre> <p>This seemed to work more consistently, but I still notice inconsistency in files getting auto-reverted. </p> <p>The one change I haven’t tried is setting <code>auto-revert-use-notify</code> to <code>nil</code>, but I was wondering if I’m missing something obvious in my setup. </p> <p>Thanks for any help!</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/jMilton13"> /u/jMilton13 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/13331mk/autorevert_mode_inconsistent/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/13331mk/autorevert_mode_inconsistent/">[comments]</a></span>